      %p
        jQuery Mobile has a rich
        %a{:href => "/mobile/docs/api/themes"} theming system
        that gives you full control of how buttons are styled. When a link is added to a container, it is automatically assigned a theme swatch letter that matches its parent bar or content box to visually integrate the button into the parent container, like a chameleon. So a button placed inside a content container with a theme of "a" (black in the default theme) will be automatically assigned the button theme of "a" (charcoal in the default theme). Here are examples of the button theme pairings in the default theme. All buttons have the same HTML markup:
      .ui-body.ui-body-a
        %h4 A swatch
        %a{"data-role" => "button", :href => "/mobile/docs/buttons"} Button
      .ui-body.ui-body-b
